.TH "ir_resize_table" 9 "ir_resize_table" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ir_resize_table \- resizes a scancode table if necessary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ir_resize_table
.BI "(struct rc_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rc_map *rc_map "  ","
.BI "gfp_t gfp_flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the rc_dev device
.IP "rc_map" 12
the rc_map to resize
.IP "gfp_flags" 12
gfp flags to use when allocating memory
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine will shrink the rc_map if it has lots of
unused entries and grow it if it is full.
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success or a negative error code
